name: Hotel Anantashram

reviews.review_text: Absolute favourite. Every single preparation is mind-blowing. Was so happy to take my husband here and have him taste what I grew up with. The taste hasn't changed in years now. Such fond memories and such a wonderful experience. Staff treat you like family!

First time tried Goan Thali. Going to Anantashram was a right decision. It was closer to where we stayed. Ordered special prawn meals, vow it was really delicious. Crab curry was awesome. Every dish served in the thali was wonderful. Prawn moilee as side dish for roti was wonderful combination. Goan Fizz was a great mocktail, I've not had such taste of cocounut milk and tender coconut water mix. Everything tasted home made without any masala and dishes are made with coconut milk. Overall worth visit and pocket friendly too

Been visiting this place for many years , best place to have a Goan fish curry rice . Food is wonderfully cooked , with you being received right at entrance by the ever smiling owner Sripad  Shetye , he really greets you well and sees to that all his customers are well attended to .

description:
**Hotel Anantashram: A Culinary Gem in Baina**

Nestled in the vibrant locale of Baina, Hotel Anantashram radiates charm and warmth, boasting an impressive rating of 4.1 from 5,256 enthusiastic reviewers. This beloved establishment has made a name for itself as a go-to destination for seafood lovers, evidenced by tags that highlight fan favorites such as "seafood" (154 mentions), "fish thali" (53 mentions), "kingfish" (25 mentions), and even a touch of "liquor" (11 mentions) on their menu. Patrons flock from near and far, eager to delve into a culinary experience that resonates with the authentic flavors of Goa.

**Ambiance & Design**  
The ambiance at Hotel Anantashram offers a welcoming embrace, exuding a nostalgic vibe that transports diners to a simpler time. The photos reveal a cozy interior adorned with vibrant local art, warm lighting, and rustic wooden elements that enhance its inviting nature. Diners are greeted with a friendly smile from the owner, Sripad Shetye, who ensures every guest feels like family from the moment they step inside. The cheerful atmosphere is complemented by an engaging selection of music, creating a lively yet relaxed backdrop to your dining experience.

**Menu & Culinary Experience**  
Diving into the menu, the restaurant showcases a culinary narrative filled with Goan heritage. Signature dishes like the Goan fish curry rice and the renowned fish thali are frequently celebrated for their rich, homemade flavors. Customer reviews glow with praise for the crab curry—a standout dish that many found "awesome"—and the special prawn meal, specifically highlighted for its delightful preparation. The presentation of dishes is inviting; vibrant colors and fresh ingredients grace each plate, with photos capturing the tantalizing allure of the prawn moilee paired perfectly with warm roti. Furthermore, vegetarians and health-conscious diners will be pleased to find options made with coconut milk that accentuate natural flavors, ensuring that every dish is both wholesome and satisfying.

**Customer Experience & Service**  
The staff at Hotel Anantashram play a pivotal role in creating an unforgettable diner experience. Guests frequently commend the friendly and attentive service, which makes them feel at home. The owner’s personal touch is evident, as he is known to warmly greet guests at the entrance, fostering a familial atmosphere. Whether opting for a reservation or walking in, visitors can expect service that is both efficient and friendly, enhancing the overall enjoyment of the meal.

**Popularity & Reviews**  
The buzz surrounding Hotel Anantashram extends beyond personal testimonials, with a wealth of positive sentiment saturating social media platforms. Many frequent diners express joy in returning to a place that has stood the test of time while maintaining the essence of home-cooked meals. The restaurant is praised for its affordability without compromising on quality, making it an attractive option for both locals and tourists alike. Although specific critic ratings and notable visits are not mentioned, the sheer volume of glowing reviews indicates a well-deserved reputation in the region.

**Utilizing Visual Content**  
The images shared by patrons vividly depict the warm ethos and culinary delights of Hotel Anantashram. From tasteful shots showcasing the intricately prepared dishes to inviting views of the cozy environment, the visuals reflect a backdrop that pairs beautifully with the incredible food. Highlights such as the beautifully plated fish thali, brimming with color and freshness, resonate with the descriptions found within the reviews, bridging the gap between expectation and reality.

In summary, Hotel Anantashram stands as a pillar of Goan cuisine, offering a delightful blend of authenticity, warmth, and flavor—making it a must-visit culinary destination in Baina. Whether it’s the rich seafood offerings or the heartfelt service, every aspect combines to create a dining experience that beckons you to return time and again.
